	<!-- New weapon groups -->
	<RulesElement internal-id="ID_XYZ_WEAPON_GROUP_5501" name="Early Firearm" type="Weapon Group" source="Weapons of the Black Powder Age" revision-date="8/3/2020 9:07:10 AM" >
		<specific name="Implement"> 0 </specific>
Early firearms use rudimentary combustible materials such as black powder to propel a projectile down a long barrel.  While they require less training and physical strength to wield effecively than a bow, they require a steady hand to aim on account of the delay between pulling the trigger and firing.  Like a crossbow, early firearms must be reloaded after each shot, but it is a prolonged process as the powder and projectile must be loaded individually from the muzzle end.
	</RulesElement>

	<RulesElement internal-id="ID_XYZ_WEAPON_GROUP_5502" name="Bayonet" type="Weapon Group" source="Weapons of the Black Powder Age" revision-date="8/3/2020 9:22:10 AM" >
		<specific name="Implement"> 0 </specific>
Bayonets are blades or spikes ranging from the size of a dagger to that of a shortsword affixed to the muzzle of a firearm.  This allows the firearm to be used as a spear should the wielder find themselves in melee combat.  Bayonets were adopted to give riflemen defense against charging foes, especially those on horseback.  They can also be dismounted and used in-hand as a normal Light Blade should the situation demand. 
	</RulesElement>


